          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "D-D"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The 2.8 MeV neutrons were obtained by",
                "bombarding a Ti-D target with a deuterium beam of 300",
                "keV energy."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "nuclide": "92-U-235",
                "field_identifier": "ENR",
                "value": 0.8949
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The uranium target with purity",
                "99.9%, is a thin slice with a side length of 1.5 cm,",
                "a thickness of 1 mm, and a mass of 0.74 g. The mass",
                "abundance of uranium isotopes includes U-234(1.15%),",
                "U-235(89.49%), U-236(0.23%) and U-238(9.13%)."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "HPGE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The HPGe gamma-ray spectrometer system is",
                "mainly composed of a GEM30P4 HPGe gamma-ray detector",
                "produced by ORTEC. The resolution of the HPGe",
                "gamma-ray detector is about 1.7 keV at 1.33 MeV.",
                "Three standard sources (Ba-133, Eu-152, and Co-60)",
                "with known activities were applied to the energy",
                "calibration and efficiency calibration."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SIBAR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Based on the He-3-particles from the D-D",
                "reaction measured by the Au-Si surface barrier",
                "detector, the average neutron flux was determined to",
                "be 9.24E8 (/s)."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "GSPEC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The uranium target was irradiated for 105 h.",
                "After cooling for 8.855 h, the counts of the",
                "full-energy peak of gamma rays emitted by various",
                "fission products were measured by HPGe gamma-ray",
                "spectroscopy."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "ASSOP"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The average neutron flux was determined based",
                "on the He-3 particles from the D-D reaction measured",
                "by the Au-Si surface barrier detector. This method",
                "also monitored the neutron flux fluctuation."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "CORRECTION": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The needed corrections contain",
                " - isotope correction of uranium,",
                " - coincidence summing correction in gamma-ray",
                "   cascade radiation,",
                " - self-absorption correction,",
                " - neutron fluency fluctuation correction."
              ]
            }
          ],
